          <msContents>
            <summary>Livre de receptes exprouveés [sic]. A collection of receipts by Ferrand and others written in the first half of the 16th cent., together with others by later hands, down to 1671: in French and Latin. Other receipts by other hands are dated: fol. xviii, 1602; fol. xxvv, 1604; fol. ii, 1638; fol. xxviv, 1666; fol. xxvii, 1668; fol. xxviiv, 1671. On the last two leaves are notes by the original compiler, dated 1550, giving details of the engagement and salaries of servants.</summary>
